photos.description:
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carotid_artery_dissection

I had this!  The big day was a week ago Wednesday â¦ got up in a haze and could barely speak.  And 30-second jobs took five minutes plus broken dishes.  Kids thought I had gone crazy.  I wasn't so confident myself â¦

Was better by the afternoon, and much better the following morning.  Thought I was pretty much recovered, although that was a tad optimistic at that point.

Perchance I was having lunch with Renaud and he figured out pretty quickly that I had had a stroke.  I was in the hospital a few hours later, and have been there, largely on my back, ever since.

I'm now up on my feet and preparing to actually leave.  Should be tomorrow or Monday.  They are nice and cautious here, and remarkably friendly.

The stroke appears to be a one-off thing with minimal chance of a repeat.  Likely combination of an early-morning fall I had while running in the near-dark, combined with more running some days later.  But, not entirely sure.

No obvious side effects.  Feeling happy and nicely rested.  All good, and thanks for reading â¦

(Oh, no questions here!)
